Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{} and sprinkle over the @Chinese Five Spice{1%sachet}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, quarter the @pear{1} lengthways (no need to peel), remove the core and thinly slice lengthways. Halve the @lime{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{64%grams}, @sambal paste{15%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and half the lime juice. Mix to combine and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the pear and @coleslaw mix{120%grams} to the bowl and stir until evenly coated. Set aside.

When the chips have 10 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @chicken gyozas{1%pack} and fry until golden on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}. Reduce the heat to medium-low, add 1 tbsp water to the pan and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until the gyozas are piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @king prawns{150%grams}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the prawns. Season and stir-fry for ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

== Hoisin Sauce ==

While the everything's cooking, pop a #small saucepan{} on medium heat.

Stir in the @hoisin sauce{60%grams} and @water for the sauce{50%ml}. Simmer until the sauce is piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and stir in the remaining lime juice. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> Add another splash of water if it's a little too thick.

== To Serve ==

Share the gyozas and prawns between your plates and spoon over the hoisin sauce. Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams}. Serve with the fries and slaw on the side. Enjoy!